    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="434"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dupuy de Lôme</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Swampscott Mass.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 8, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary</hi>: Acknowledging receipt of your note dated
                    5th instant, I have the honor to tender to your excellency my thanks to the <pb
                        facs="0465" n="1199" xml:id="pg_1199"/> Government of the United States and
                    to the Federal authorities who have intervened in the capture of arms and
                    ammunition near Cedar Keys.</p>
                <p>At the same time I take pleasure in undertaking that the Spanish consul in
                    Florida will make in due time the sworn statement which you mention as necessary
                    in order to establish judicial proceedings.</p>
                <p>I avail myself, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Dupuy de Lôme</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
